John F. ROSIER and Jim E. Williams, Sr., Appellants, v. UNITED STATES of America, Appellee. No. 6332. Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. April 9, 1932. W. K. Zewadski, Jr., and Wm. C. Pierce, both of Tampa, Fla., for appellants. W. P. Hughes, U. S. Atty., of Jacksonville, Fla.

Before BRYAN, FOSTER, and SIBLEY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The judgment is affirmed.
